      <item>
        <title>Canning Thunderbird&#39;s startpage</title>
        <dc:creator><![CDATA[HulaHoop]]></dc:creator>
        <description><![CDATA[
            <p>I think we should disable the <a href="https://user-media-prod-cdn.itsre-sumo.mozilla.net/uploads/gallery/images/2018-11-21-20-34-29-70625e.png">welcome page</a> it fetches from Thunderbird’s website to minimize attack surface. Sure it connects over TLS, but this isn’t secure in certain threat models against advanced adversaries.</p>
<p>We can replace it with custom project art instead or just opt to retire it completely.</p>
<p><strong><code>mailnews.start_page.enabled -&gt; false</code></strong></p>
